      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 125: This marks the CMake configure step as a recursive command. The `+` prefix is only needed on commands that invoke `$(MAKE)`; on non-make commands it also forces execution under `make -n/-t/-q`, so a dry-run can unexpectedly create/modify the build directory. Remove the prefix from the configure step and keep it only on the install make invocation.\n```suggestion\n\tcd $\u003c \u0026\u0026 cd build \u0026\u0026 $(HOSTVARS) $(CMAKE) .. $(OPENCV_CMAKECONF)\n```",
